ENTRY            D4439   20260209   20260508   20260508       D151
SUBENT        D4439001   20260209   20260508   20260508       D151
BIB                 13         30
TITLE      Alpha-particles induced nuclear reactions on zinc:
           Experimental and theoretical evaluation
AUTHOR     (A.Elbinawi,B.M.Ali,F.Ditroi,M.Al-Abyad)
INSTITUTE  (3EGYCAI,3HUNDEB)
REFERENCE  (J,NP/A,1063,123211,2025)
           #doi:10.1016/j.nuclphysa.2025.123211
FACILITY   (CYCLO,3HUNDEB)
EXP-YEAR   (2014)
SAMPLE     High chemical purity (99.99%), 25 um thick, self
           supporting natural isotopic composition Zn
DETECTOR   (HPGE)
METHOD     (ACTIV)
ERR-ANALYS (EN-ERR)
           Including the primary beam energy uncertainty and the
           uncertainty of target thickness (0.6-0.98 MeV)
           (ERR-T)
           The total uncertainty of the cross-section values
            (16-21%) is estimated using the standard method, which
           involves taking the quadratic sum of the independently
           contributing parameters.
           (ERR-S,12.0,18.0) statistical uncertainty (12-18%)
           (ERR-1) beam intensity (7.0%)
           (ERR-2) target thickness (3.0%)
           (ERR-3) detection efficiency (7.0%)
           (ERR-4) half-life (3.0%)
COMMENT    By Ferenc Ditroi (2026-02-11):
           The gamma lines used for cross section determination
            are unknown.
STATUS     (TABLE,,A.Elbinawi+,J,NP/A,1063,123211,2025) Table 2
HISTORY    (20260204C) TT
